<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title><%= pageTitle %> | MyTaxCalcs</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Use the free payroll tax calculator to estimate federal withholding, Social Security tax, Medicare tax, state withholding, and net paycheck amount.">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

  <meta name="google-site-verification" content="TT2j7SglafccBK-Nfk4l1XVIDXEJdSmyQJf2wL9QY0o" />

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">

  <script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5193834725888549"
     crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <header class="small-header">
    <nav class="nav">
      <a href="/" class="logo">
        <span class="logo-icon">💵</span>
        <span>MyTaxCalcs</span>
      </a>

      <div class="nav-links">
  <a href="/">Home</a>
  <a href="/calculators">Calculators</a>
  <a href="/california-income-tax-calculator">States</a>
  <a href="/about">About</a>
  <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
</div>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="container two-column">
    <section class="card">
      <h1>Payroll Tax Calculator</h1>
      <p>Estimate paycheck withholding, FICA taxes, optional state withholding, and take-home pay.</p>

      <form method="POST" action="/payroll-tax-calculator" class="form">
        <label>
          Gross pay per paycheck
          <input type="number" name="grossPay" value="<%= form.grossPay || '' %>" placeholder="2500" min="0" step="0.01" required>
        </label>

        <label>
          Pay frequency
          <select name="payFrequency">
            <option value="weekly" <%= form.payFrequency === "weekly" ? "selected" : "" %>>Weekly</option>
            <option value="biweekly" <%= !form.payFrequency || form.payFrequency === "biweekly" ? "selected" : "" %>>Biweekly</option>
            <option value="semimonthly" <%= form.payFrequency === "semimonthly" ? "selected" : "" %>>Semi-monthly</option>
            <option value="monthly" <%= form.payFrequency === "monthly" ? "selected" : "" %>>Monthly</option>
            <option value="annual" <%= form.payFrequency === "annual" ? "selected" : "" %>>Annual</option>
          </select>
        </label>

        <label>
          Filing status
          <select name="filingStatus">
            <option value="single" <%= form.filingStatus === "single" ? "selected" : "" %>>Single</option>
            <option value="marriedJoint" <%= form.filingStatus === "marriedJoint" ? "selected" : "" %>>Married Filing Jointly</option>
            <option value="marriedSeparate" <%= form.filingStatus === "marriedSeparate" ? "selected" : "" %>>Married Filing Separately</option>
            <option value="headHousehold" <%= form.filingStatus === "headHousehold" ? "selected" : "" %>>Head of Household</option>
          </select>
        </label>

        <label>
          Pre-tax deductions per paycheck
          <input type="number" name="preTaxDeductions" value="<%= form.preTaxDeductions || '' %>" placeholder="200" min="0" step="0.01">
        </label>

        <label>
          Post-tax deductions per paycheck
          <input type="number" name="postTaxDeductions" value="<%= form.postTaxDeductions || '' %>" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01">
        </label>

        <label>
          Extra federal withholding per paycheck
          <input type="number" name="federalExtraWithholding" value="<%= form.federalExtraWithholding || '' %>" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01">
        </label>

        <label>
          State withholding rate (%)
          <input type="number" name="stateTaxRate" value="<%= form.stateTaxRate || '' %>" placeholder="5" min="0" step="0.001">
        </label>

        <label>
          Year-to-date wages before this paycheck
          <input type="number" name="ytdWagesBeforeThisPaycheck" value="<%= form.ytdWagesBeforeThisPaycheck || '' %>" placeholder="0" min="0" step="0.01">
        </label>

        <button type="submit">Calculate Payroll Taxes</button>
      </form>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Estimated Results</h2>

      <% if (!result) { %>
        <p class="muted">Enter paycheck details to estimate payroll taxes and net pay.</p>
      <% } else { %>
        <div class="results">
          <p><span>Tax year:</span> <strong><%= result.taxYear %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Gross pay:</span> <strong>$<%= result.grossPay.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Taxable pay estimate:</span> <strong>$<%= result.taxablePay.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Federal withholding estimate:</span> <strong>$<%= result.estimatedFederalWithholding.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Social Security tax:</span> <strong>$<%= result.socialSecurityTax.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Medicare tax:</span> <strong>$<%= result.medicareTax.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Additional Medicare tax:</span> <strong>$<%= result.additionalMedicareTax.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
          <p><span>State withholding estimate:</span> <strong>$<%= result.stateWithholding.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Total tax estimate:</span> <strong>$<%= result.totalTaxes.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Post-tax deductions:</span> <strong>$<%= result.postTaxDeductions.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Estimated net pay:</span> <strong>$<%= result.netPay.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Estimated annual net pay:</span> <strong>$<%= result.estimatedAnnualNetPay.toFixed(2) %></strong></p>
        </div>
      <% } %>

      <p class="disclaimer">Estimate only. Actual payroll withholding may vary based on Form W-4, benefits, state rules, local taxes, and employer payroll settings.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <section class="container content seo-content">
    <p class="eyebrow dark">Payroll Tax Guide</p>
    <h2>How this payroll tax calculator works</h2>
    <p>
      This payroll tax calculator estimates paycheck deductions by annualizing your gross pay,
      applying a simplified federal income tax estimate, calculating Social Security and Medicare
      taxes, and subtracting optional state withholding and post-tax deductions.
    </p>

    <div class="seo-grid">
      <div class="seo-mini-card">
        <h3>Federal withholding</h3>
        <p>
          The federal withholding estimate is based on annualized taxable pay, filing status,
          the standard deduction, and federal tax brackets. It is not a full Form W-4 calculation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seo-mini-card">
        <h3>FICA taxes</h3>
        <p>
          FICA generally includes Social Security tax and Medicare tax. Social Security has an annual
          wage base limit, while Medicare tax does not.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seo-mini-card">
        <h3>Net paycheck</h3>
        <p>
          Estimated net pay is calculated by subtracting pre-tax deductions, estimated taxes,
          and post-tax deductions from gross pay.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Payroll tax FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What taxes usually come out of a paycheck?</h3>
        <p>
          Common paycheck deductions include federal income tax withholding, Social Security tax,
          Medicare tax, state income tax withholding, local taxes, benefits, retirement contributions,
          and other deductions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is this the same as an official payroll withholding calculation?</h3>
        <p>
          No. This calculator provides a simplified estimate. Actual payroll withholding may depend
          on your Form W-4, employer payroll system, pre-tax benefit rules, state rules, and local taxes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is Social Security tax?</h3>
        <p>
          Social Security tax is part of FICA payroll tax. Employees pay a percentage of covered wages
          up to the annual Social Security wage base.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is Medicare tax?</h3>
        <p>
          Medicare tax is another part of FICA payroll tax. It generally applies to all covered wages,
          and higher wages may also be subject to Additional Medicare Tax withholding.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Why is my actual paycheck different?</h3>
        <p>
          Actual paycheck amounts may differ because of health insurance, retirement deductions,
          employer benefits, local taxes, W-4 settings, payroll rounding, bonuses, overtime, and other items.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</p>
  </section>

